The UK still has:
• no legal maximum bus cab temperature;
• no dedicated bus driver heat safety framework;
• no nationally enforceable cooling standards;
• no DVSA standards on excessive cab temperatures;
• and no nationally agreed operational heatwave procedures for the bus industry.
 
Things that will need to be considered are:
• driver cab cooling;
• occupational heat protection;
• climate control standards;
• fatigue management;
• and heatwave operational procedures.
 
Let's make change!
